The paper focuses on the architecture and interaction of mobile devices with the cloud, specifically in the context of artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the performance evaluation of prevalent commercial applications and intelligent frameworks, which falls under cs.MOBILE. The paper also touches upon issues and challenges related to the area of mobile intelligence, which can be categorized under cs.SY (systems and control) and cs.DC (distributed, parallel, and cluster computing). Finally, the paper conducts experiments to evaluate the performance of mobile intelligence, which can be classified under cs.NI (networking and internet architecture).
